																		Oh wait, I wasn&#039;t the only one with this problem?
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/soullesssingularity" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(637830); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=637830&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204250" alt="SoullessSingularity" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=637830)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/soullesssingularity" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(637830); return false;" >SoullessSingularity</a></span> <span class="odate time_1350719083 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">20 Oct 2012 07:44</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1592644">
									

<p>I thought I was the only one who had problems with this tale.</p>
<p>It reads so boring that by paragraph 4 I scrolled up, downvoted, skimmed the rest for anything that made up for the borefest and found nothing. If you want to outline a headcanon you can do that by cutting out the introductory narrative. The real meat is the tabbed stuff. The rest is just fleshy tumors growing off. At first I thought this was because I was in a bad mood and at work, so my brain didn't operate correctly in analyzing the narrative. Now that I'm home and marginally in a better mood I realize that, no, my original reading was correct and this reads like some boring textbook.</p>
<p>There are no characters. Just faceless cardboard cutouts of people, a blank white frame around a picture. Except the picture is so small and the frame is much too large. This, paired with a narrator that has absolutely no weight in his words (no twinges of word play, no personality, the barest attempt at humor (doesn't work), no different ways to say things, colloquialisms, nothing) makes it a chore to read and by the time I got to the 'real' tale, I wanted nothing to do with it at all.</p>

							</div>

										<div class="signature">
					<hr class="signature-separator"/>
					

<p>Living the dream, or dreaming the life?</p>

				</div>
					
					
