				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thedeadlymoose" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(732274); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=732274&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204250" alt="thedeadlymoose" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=732274)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/thedeadlymoose" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(732274); return false;" >thedeadlymoose</a></span> <span class="odate time_1350720840 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">20 Oct 2012 08:14</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1592652">
									

<p>Gotta agree with Soulless here. This is tedious as fuck. At least in part. I only read the first half (edit: third?) of it. I didn't even get to the pseudocanon stuff.</p>
<p>I <em>do</em> plan to come back and read the rest, based on the enthusiastic reactions to the pseudocanon, but I would seriously advise rewriting at least the part that I managed to read. I don't really agree with Soulless on one point - that you should cut the narrative entirely - rather, I think that you should fix it. Just think of how much better this piece would be with a narrative that's more fun to read, or a narrator that we actually want to spend time with?</p>
<p>(No vote until I finish reading later.)</p>

							</div>

								
